2025: Foundation, Education Launch, and Structural Setup

Education

Develop introductory educational materials in Haitian Creole explaining blockchain, cUSD, CELO, ReFi, and their relevance for Haiti.

Establish the CeloHT Basic Academy with small-group sessions via WhatsApp, Telegram, and Zoom.

Create digital content (videos, documents, tutorials) for public access.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Identify reliable community agents across key regions to handle:

transfers,

cUSD payments,

basic conversions between cUSD, USD, and HTG.


Establish the “CeloHT Field Agents Network” with clear roles and responsibilities.


Environmental Programs

Develop the first environmental plan, including selected regions for tree planting and nursery preparation.

Initiate awareness programs on “Green Blockchain” and the “Zero Carbon Vision.”




2026: Community Development and Pilot Programs

Education

Launch recurring weekly training sessions covering both technical and social aspects of blockchain.

Publish a free digital educational library on the official CeloHT website.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Formalize operational procedures for field agents, including:

security protocols,

transaction verification steps,

proper cUSD handling.


Start a pilot program enabling community members to pay for small local services using cUSD.


Environmental Programs

Launch the first CeloHT nursery (small scale: 500–1,000 plants).

Build a volunteer environmental group for community support.




2027: Technical Structure, Community Strengthening, and Nursery Expansion

Education

Publish the official booklet “Blockchain for Haiti.”

Train 10–20 educational ambassadors across different regions.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Expand the Field Agents Network to more departments.

Implement monthly operational reporting:

transfer volumes,

cUSD usage trends,

local market observations.



Environmental Programs

Establish 2–3 regional nurseries.

Begin official tree-planting programs with documented tracking.




2028: Regional Expansion and Advanced Development

Education

Launch an online training platform offering self-paced courses.

Provide specialized courses in digital finance, security, and Web3 entrepreneurship.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Strengthen the agent network and assign each agent a geographic responsibility area.

Introduce a transparent public activity report without any personal data.


Environmental Programs

Professionalize nursery management with tracking sheets and monitoring protocols.

Launch the community program “Plant a Tree, Protect Your Future.”




2029: Professionalization and Impact Measurement

Education

Publish a formal education impact report (2025–2029).

Expand CeloHT curriculum to high schools, vocational centers, and universities.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Create an “Operational Handbook” for all field agents.

Increase cUSD usage within local small businesses.


Environmental Programs

Document the total number of trees planted since 2025.

Introduce simple monitoring tools (GPS tags or ID codes) for tree tracking.




2030: Digital Expansion and Large-Scale Impact

Education

Launch a trilingual (Creole + French+English) education platform.

Introduce advanced programs covering ReFi, sustainable development, and digital economic growth.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Operate a strong nationwide micro-agent network.

Develop simple digital tools (dashboard or app) to support field agent operations.

Formalize partnerships with local small enterprises.


Environmental Programs

Expand reforestation goals:

target 50,000–100,000 trees planted within 7 years depending on capacity.


Launch “Green Youth Days” environmental awareness program.




2031: Consolidation, Strong Governance, and International Structure

Education

Establish formal collaborations with universities and international NGOs.

Introduce the official CeloHT Certification Program.


Financial Network / Field Agents

Recognize the field agent network as the “National CeloHT Micro-Network.”

Publish annual financial transparency reports.


Environmental Programs

Ensure nurseries become self-sustaining with local management teams.

Publish the first “CeloHT Environmental Impact Report.”





2032: Autonomy, Global Recognition, and Measurable Results

Education

Position CeloHT as the leading blockchain education ecosystem for Haiti.

Publish the “CeloHT 7-Year Global Impact Report.”


Financial Network / Field Agents

Achieve a fully autonomous, self-sustained financial agent network.

Implement long-term operational independence without reliance on grants.


Environmental Programs

Establish national-level reforestation programs.

Position CeloHT as a major Green Blockchain actor within the Caribbean region.
